{"type": "assistant", "message": {"id": "msg_1783772697730", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "tool_use", "id": "chatcmpl-tool-a916014ea7ab73c9", "name": "Agent", "input": {"description": "Fetch arXiv paper PDF", "prompt": "I need to download and read the PDF of arXiv paper 2607.08526v1. Try these approaches in order:\n\n1. First try: `wget -q -O /tmp/paper_2607.08526.pdf \"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2607.08526v1\"` then check if the file is a valid PDF with `file /tmp/paper_2607.08526.pdf`\n2. If that fails, try: `curl -sL -o /tmp/paper_2607.08526.pdf \"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2607.08526v1\"` then check with `file /tmp/paper_2607.08526.pdf`\n3. Also try fetching the abstract page: `curl -sL \"https://arxiv.org/abs/2607.08526v1\"`\n\nReport back: the PDF file path if successful, the file size, and the first few pages of text content if you can extract it (use `pdftotext /tmp/paper_2607.08526.pdf /tmp/paper_2607.08526.txt` if available, then read the first 200 lines). If PDF download fails, report the full HTML of the abstract page.", "subagent_type": "general-purpose"}}], "model": "GLM-5.2-w4a8", "stop_reason": null, "stop_sequence": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 0, "output_tokens": 0, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 0, "cache_read_input_tokens": 0}, "context_management": null}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "86d5cef4-7ac1-4410-82b1-59695be50d5b", "uuid": "4fe92150-906e-4a1a-a6a5-1c78afbbc703"}
