{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-b0edcbd54ed9d493", "type": "tool_result", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "## Result: `wiki_query` MCP tool is NOT available\n\nI checked the available tool set thoroughly, including a search of all deferred tools and skills. There is no `wiki_query` MCP tool registered in this environment.\n\n**What I checked:**\n- The top-level tool list in my system prompt (no `wiki_query` present)\n- `ToolSearch` with query `\"wiki_query\"` → \"No matching deferred tools found\"\n- `ToolSearch` with query `\"+wiki query knowledge base\"` → \"No matching deferred tools found\"\n- `ToolSearch` with query `\"select:paper-wiki,free-search,tavily-search\"` → returned no schemas (these are skills, not callable tools)\n- `ToolSearch` with query `\"mcp wiki query omc\"` → no results\n\n**Closest available alternative:** A `paper-wiki` **skill** exists (loaded above), which operates a local personal paper knowledge base at `/inspire/qb-ilm/project/video-generation/chenxie-25019/hyr/cc-research/my-paper-wiki`. However, its interface does not match the `wiki_query({query, tags})` signature you specified — it uses `uv run paper-wiki search --concept \"...\"` / `--dataset \"...\"` / `--paper <arxiv_id>` against a local SQLite/yaml-backed store of arxiv papers you have personally ingested. It is not the OMC Wiki MCP server.\n\n## Verbatim results for the 10 requested calls\n\n| # | Call | Result |\n|---|------|--------|\n| 1 | `wiki_query({ query: \"on-device audio generation edge deployment SOTA\", tags: [\"audio\", \"edge\"] })` | **TOOL NOT AVAILABLE** — not executed |\n| 2 | `wiki_query({ query: \"Stable Audio 3 text-to-music model\", tags: [\"audio\", \"generation\"] })` | **TOOL NOT AVAILABLE** — not executed |\n| 3 | `wiki_query({ query: \"model quantization edge deployment native runtime\", tags: [\"quantization\", \"systems\"] })` | **TOOL NOT AVAILABLE** — not executed |\n| 4 | `wiki_query({ query: \"activation steering audio music generation control\", tags: [\"steering\", \"audio\"] })` | **TOOL NOT AVAILABLE** — not executed |\n| 5 | `wiki_query({ query: \"dependency-free C runtime inference llama.cpp ggml\", tags: [\"systems\", \"inference\"] })` | **TOOL NOT AVAILABLE** — not executed |\n| 6 | `wiki_query({ query: \"diffusion model quantization post-training\", tags: [\"quantization\", \"diffusion\"] })` | **TOOL NOT AVAILABLE** — not executed |\n| 7 | `wiki_query({ query: \"sonic seasoning taste music crossmodal\", tags: [\"audio\", \"psychophysics\"] })` | **TOOL NOT AVAILABLE** — not executed |\n| 8 | `wiki_query({ query: \"audio diffusion transformer edge device deployment baseline\", tags: [\"audio\", \"systems\"] })` | **TOOL NOT AVAILABLE** — not executed |\n| 9 | `wiki_query({ query: \"llama.cpp whisper.cpp native runtime quantization prior work\", tags: [\"systems\"] })` | **TOOL NOT AVAILABLE** — not executed |\n| 10 | `wiki_query({ query: \"FAD Frechet Audio Distance CLAP evaluation audio quality\", tags: [\"audio\", \"evaluation\"] })` | **TOOL NOT AVAILABLE** — not executed |\n\n## How to proceed\n\nTo unblock your paper review, here are the realistic options. Tell me which you want and I'll execute:\n\n1. **Find and connect the OMC Wiki MCP server.** If there is an MCP server config file somewhere on disk (e.g. `~/.claude/mcp_servers.json`, a `.mcp.json` in the repo, or a project-level settings file), point me at it or authorize me to look, and I can verify whether the `wiki_query` tool can be registered. It may simply need to be started/added to the harness config.\n2. **Use the `paper-wiki` skill as a substitute.** I can run `uv run paper-wiki search --concept \"<query>\"` for each of the 10 query strings against your local arxiv knowledge base. Note: this only searches papers you have personally ingested, not the OMC Wiki, and it does not support tag filtering — only concept/dataset/paper-id filters. Results would not be equivalent to `wiki_query` output.\n3. **Use `tavily-search` (web search) as a substitute** for the portions of the queries that are about public information (e.g. Stable Audio 3, llama.cpp, FAD). This would give web results, not wiki results.\n\nI have not run any of the 10 queries against a substitute source, because you asked me to report results verbatim and to report clearly if the tool is unavailable — substituting a different tool silently would falsify that report. Awaiting your instruction on which option to take."}, {"type": "text", "text": "agentId: ac64b91e418fc57eb (use SendMessage with to: 'ac64b91e418fc57eb' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 11088\ntool_uses: 5\nduration_ms: 87877</usage>"}]}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "86d5cef4-7ac1-4410-82b1-59695be50d5b", "uuid": "38974c1f-fdca-4e4d-b026-650da5e75f2f", "timestamp": "2026-07-11T12:30:31.478Z", "tool_use_result": {"status": "completed", "prompt": "I need to query the OMC Wiki knowledge base for a paper review. Use the wiki_query MCP tool to run the following queries. Report ALL results verbatim, including empty results or errors.\n\nRun these wiki_query calls (if the tool is available):\n\n1. wiki_query({ query: \"on-device audio generation edge deployment SOTA\", tags: [\"audio\", \"edge\"] })\n2. wiki_query({ query: \"Stable Audio 3 text-to-music model\", tags: [\"audio\", \"generation\"] })\n3. wiki_query({ query: \"model quantization edge deployment native runtime\", tags: [\"quantization\", \"systems\"] })\n4. wiki_query({ query: \"activation steering audio music generation control\", tags: [\"steering\", \"audio\"] })\n5. wiki_query({ query: \"dependency-free C runtime inference llama.cpp ggml\", tags: [\"systems\", \"inference\"] })\n6. wiki_query({ query: \"diffusion model quantization post-training\", tags: [\"quantization\", \"diffusion\"] })\n7. wiki_query({ query: \"sonic seasoning taste music crossmodal\", tags: [\"audio\", \"psychophysics\"] })\n8. wiki_query({ quer