e `paper-wiki` skill as a substitute.** I can run `uv run paper-wiki search --concept \"<query>\"` for each of the 10 query strings against your local arxiv knowledge base. Note: this only searches papers you have personally ingested, not the OMC Wiki, and it does not support tag filtering — only concept/dataset/paper-id filters. Results would not be equivalent to `wiki_query` output.\n3. **Use `tavily-search` (web search) as a substitute** for the portions of the queries that are about public information (e.g. Stable Audio 3, llama.cpp, FAD). This would give web results, not wiki results.\n\nI have not run any of the 10 queries against a substitute source, because you asked me to report results verbatim and to report clearly if the tool is unavailable — substituting a different tool silently would falsify that report. Awaiting your instruction on which option to take."}], "totalDurationMs": 87877, "totalTokens": 11088, "totalToolUseCount": 5, "usage": {"input_tokens": 9687, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 0, "cache_read_input_tokens": 0, "output_tokens": 1401, "server_tool_use": {"web_search_requests": 0, "web_fetch_requests": 0}, "service_tier": "standard", "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 0, "ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 0}, "inference_geo": "", "iterations": [], "speed": "standard"}}}
